          <p>Shri Guru Raghavendra Swamy also known as Parimalacharya is a respected 16th century saint who was known for preaching Madhwa Philosophy. He is considered as one of the avatara of King Prahlada. He ascended Brindavana at Mantralayam in present day Andhra Pradesh in 1671.  </p>
            <p>Brief Story:
               Sri Raghavendra Swami was born as Sri Venkata Natha (Venkata Ramana), the second son of Sri Thimanna Bhatta and Smt. Gopikamba on Thursday, Sukla Navami of Phalguna month in 1595, in Mrigashīrsha Nakshatra, at Bhuvanagiri, near Chidambaram in Tamil Nadu. Venkatanatha had two siblings: Gururaja and Venkatamba. Venkatanatha's education was undertaken by his brother-in-law Lakshminarasimhacharya, after the early demise of his father. 
               Venkatanatha was married to Saraswathi and had a son Lakshminarayana.  He was a disciple of Sudhindra Tirtha, the pontiff of Kumbakonam mutt.  Venkatanatha succeeded him as the pontiff the mutt and took on the name Raghavendra Tirtha. Guru  Raghavendra was great in every respect. He was siddha Purusha (God realised person). He went on many pilgrimages, and performed many miracles, Blind got their eyesight, Deaf could hear.



                Raghavendra Thirtha enterted brindavana alive on shraavana bahula bidige. He was succeeded by his disciple Yogeendra Tirtha.

